Instagram is introducing a new Saved Posts&#8217; feature that lets users bookmark photos to view later.The platform has added a new icon to posts to its 10.2 version, allowing users to save images to a private tab on their profile, visible only to them.The news comes days after Apple revealed the social media app was its fourth most downloaded in 2016, following Snapchat, Messenger and Pokemon Go. Instagram 10.2 is now available for iOS, Android and Windows 10.-Relaxnews